<item>
            <title>[JDK-8297288] Example code in Scanner class</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8297288</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>There is one using `System.in` as:&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
With JEP 400, the default charset and console charset may differ, thus this example may result in an unexpected one if the user tries to read a String from the scanner. This should be replaced with:&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Scanner sc = new Scanner(Console.reader())&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
so that the user would not have to take encoding into consideration.</description>
